<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-06-21T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-06-21T19:00:00-05:00" n="382" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701. 4112/90: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-06-21T20:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 21,
                                        1924—8 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>326. Your 228, June 20, 3 p.m. Department assumes that Cummins is now eh
                            route to Laredo and therefore representations directed in Department’s
                            319, June 19, 7 p.m. apparently need not be made. However, Department
                            depends upon your discretion in case of emergency before Cummins leaves
                            Mexican soil.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>